                <tr><td><strong>SGB 2024-25 (Series II)</strong></td><td>₹6,263</td><td>₹7,250</td><td>15.8%</td><td>~20.8% (2 yr)</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <p><em>*Gold price as of April 2026 (₹7,250/gram for 999 purity). Returns include estimated 2.5% annual interest. Actual returns vary by exact issue and redemption dates.</em></p>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Benefits</span><h2>Why Invest in Sovereign Gold Bonds?</h2></div>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Double Income: Interest + Gold Appreciation</strong><p>SGBs are the only gold investment that pays you interest — 2.5% per annum (paid semi-annually) on top of gold price movements. Physical gold, gold ETFs, and digital gold offer zero interest income.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Tax-Free Capital Gains at Maturity</strong><p>Capital gains arising from redemption of SGBs at maturity (8 years) are completely exempt from income tax. This is a massive advantage over physical gold and gold mutual funds where long-term capital gains are taxed at 12.5%.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Sovereign Guarantee by Government of India</strong><p>SGBs carry the sovereign guarantee of the Government of India for both the principal and interest. At maturity, you receive the prevailing gold price guaranteed by the government, eliminating any counterparty risk.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>No Storage Cost or Risk</strong><p>Unlike physical gold, SGBs are held in electronic (demat) form or as certificates. There are no storage costs, no risk of theft, and no concerns about purity — the bonds are linked to 999 purity gold price.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Collateral for Loans</strong><p>SGBs can be used as collateral to obtain loans from banks and financial institutions. The loan-to-value ratio is the same as that applicable for ordinary gold loans, adding to their utility beyond just investment returns.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Tradeable on Stock Exchanges</strong><p>SGBs are listed on NSE and BSE, allowing you to exit before the 8-year maturity through secondary market trading. Early redemption is also available with RBI after the 5th year from the date of issue.</p></div></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">How to Invest</span><h2>How to Buy Sovereign Gold Bonds</h2></div>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">1</div><h3>Check Issue Window</h3><p>RBI announces SGB tranches periodically. Check the current tranche dates, issue price, and application window. You can also buy existing SGBs on stock exchanges anytime.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">2</div><h3>Apply Online</h3><p>Apply through your bank's net banking, stock broker, or RBI Retail Direct. Online applications get a ₹50/gram discount on the issue price. Minimum is 1 gram, maximum 4 kg per individual per year.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">3</div><h3>Get Allotment</h3><p>SGBs are allotted on the settlement date and credited to your demat account. A Certificate of Holding is also issued. Start earning 2.5% interest from the date of issue.</p></div>
              <div class="step-card"><div class="step-num">4</div><h3>Hold & Earn</h3><p>Receive semi-annual interest in your bank account. At maturity (8 years), receive the prevailing gold price tax-free. Or exit after 5 years via RBI or anytime via stock exchange.</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>

